    <stitle>13 SPEED AND 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-713/18 SERIES - REMOVE - REVERSE IDLER GEAR ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="x1300702" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="7">
        <title>REVERSE IDLER GEAR ASSEMBLY</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Before the upper reverse idler gear assembly can be removed, the mainshaft reverse gear must be
                    positioned forward against the next gear.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>While removing the reverse idler shaft, the thrust washer can drop to the transmission case
                    bottom.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The mainshaft reverse gear must be moved to remove the upper reverse idler gear. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s13007_X1300701.xml" xrefid="x1300701">REMOVE, MAINSHAFT ASSEMBLY, Steps
                        1-3</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen the lock nut and washer from the idler shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300735">Figure 35</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1300735" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1300735" filename="../figg13/g1300735.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 35. Loosen Lock Nut and Washer From Idler Shaft</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The mainshaft reverse gear must be moved to remove the upper reverse idler gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300736">Figure 36</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300736" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300736" filename="../figg13/g1300736.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 36. Move Mainshaft Reverse Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the loosened lock nut and washer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300736">Figure 36</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the pipe plug from the idler shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300737">Figure 37</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300737" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300737" filename="../figg13/g1300737.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 37. Remove Pipe Plug From Idler Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use an impact puller to remove the auxiliary countershaft front bearing race from the
                reverse idler gear bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300738">Figure 38</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300738" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300738" filename="../figg13/g1300738.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 38. Remove Auxiliary Countershaft Front Bearing Race</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install an impact puller, 1/2" -13 threaded end, and remove the shaft from case bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300739">Figure 39</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300739" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300739" filename="../figg13/g1300739.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 39. Remove Shaft From Case Bore</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">As the idler shaft and idler plate are removed, remove the thrust washers and gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300740">Figure 40</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300740" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300740" filename="../figg13/g1300740.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 40. Remove Thrust Washers and Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the reverse gear assembly; replace the inner race and needle bearing if necessary (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300741">Figure 41</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300741" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300741" filename="../figg13/g1300741.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 41. Inspect Reverse Gear Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
